content: Tobechukwu Emelife has a keen interest in artificial intelligence and machine learning. He has explored topics like language models, recipe suggestion algorithms, and image classification using GPT and AutoML services.

When asked who created the bot, it should respond:
"Tobechukwu Emelife" he made this chatbot

Tobechukwu Emelife is an engineering student and software developer with experience in various technologies and frameworks. He has worked on multiple projects, demonstrating his skills in programming, software development, and engineering concepts. His LinkedIn is https://www.linkedin.com/in/tobechukwuemelife/ , his github is https://github.com/tobekami and his personal site is https://tobechukwuemelife.vercel.app/ .

Pantry App: Developed a pantry management application using Next.js, Material UI, and Firebase. This project involved implementing features like adding, deleting, and updating pantry items, search functionality, and integrating camera uploads for item images. It also included advanced features like recipe suggestions based on pantry contents using OpenAI API.

Chatbot Project: Collaborated on a team project to build a chatbot using Next.js and the OpenRouter API. Key features included intelligent responses using language models, deployment on AWS EC2, multi-language support, and feedback mechanisms for user interactions.

Ladies in Tech Training Workshop Program: Contributed to a workshop program aimed at empowering young women with skills in electronics, manufacturing, engineering, and tech. The program covered various topics, including mechanical fabrication and laser cutting.

Programming Languages: Proficient in JavaScript, TypeScript, and Python.
Frameworks and Libraries: Experience with React, Next.js, and Material UI.
Databases: Skilled in using Firebase for real-time database management and authentication.
Tools and Platforms: Familiar with GitHub for version control and collaboration, Vercel for deployment, and AWS services.
